CCa ServicesYou are here:HomeCCa Services












“We work hard, so you don’t have to”
We begin a long-term advisory relationship by taking a detailed look at your overall financial situation in order to:

Understand your goals and what is truly important to you.
Identify opportunities and risks particular to your circumstances.
Develop strategies to help you reach your goals.

Whether you are an individual investor seeking wealth management and financial planning services, or a family or corporate fiduciary requiring consultative and management support of your fiduciary responsibilities, CCa can help.







Wealth Management
We typically address several major areas of wealth management and financial planning, including:

Asset Allocation
Implementation
Monitoring of Managers
Tax Management
Investment & Stock-Option Planning
Estate Planning
Cash Analysis
Long-Term Capital Needs
Risk Management
Charitable Giving
Social Security Claiming Strategies
Post-Retirement Investment Strategies
Retirement Feasibility Analysis






Fiduciary Services
We can help fiduciaries structure and monitor retirement plans, family trusts, and charitable trust investment programs, with the following services:

Experts on fiduciary rules
Consulting for fiduciary requirements
Analyzing assets
Proposing suitable asset allocation
Controlling investment risk
Evaluating investment returns
Oversee investment expenses
Analyzing non-traditional investments
Institute prudent procedures
Establish investment “best practices”








Our firm’s experience is deep, broad and practical. CCa acts not only as an advisor but also as an independent fiduciary decision maker when the fund’s regular fiduciaries require additional support and management.
 
We know — and deliver to our clients — investment “best practices”












































